			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">That's funny somebody thinks mobs should get tweaked to be magic resistant/immune accordingly to the incomming melee resist. 
<br />

<br />
Oddly...high resist rates & magic immunity on mobs has been the case since the introduction of a MMORPG called Everquest around 5 years ago.
<br />

<br />
Today, there are an overabundance of mobs that are IMMUNE to particular spell resist checks and/or types, mobs that innately mitigate spells...especially boss mobs.  Unfortunately, casters can't say "oh well, i can't cast on this so I'll jump in and do 50-70dps melee damage."  When mobs like this are the target - it's screwdom for the caster.  Unless of course you are a mage and can send in your pet (the BEST pet in the game) for a 40dps burst of 12 seconds until it gets pwned by an AE or rampage.
<br />

<br />
Also, just your typical mobs today in PoP are heavily resistant towards particular checks - depending on the mob and zone.  BoT is one great example, with each wing comprising of a different resist check (West wing is IMMUNE to all fire damage - major suck for the mage while east wing is just damn uber for the mage with their low FR).  Just one example you can verify easily.
<br />

<br />
So...just because a mob may require a particular weapon type to be succeptable - be happy you have access to that weapon skill.  It's not anybody's fault but your own that you lack the insight to keep all available skills up to date, or that you lack weapon variety.  Do you now still wish mobs to be tweaked to magic resists to be on par with melee resists?   I would love it - because it would essentially make all my mage's spells -500 bane...or to clarify it would reduce my resists by a HUGE margin.  I would become a god.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
